Top 10 Hedge Funds’ Profits Surpass Those of Banks, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-03-02T07:37:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-02/top-10-hedge-funds-profits-surpass-those-of-banks-ft-reports.html
The top 10  hedge funds , measured by
total dollar returns since they started, made profits for their
investors of $28 billion in the second half of 2010, the
Financial Times reported, citing research by LCH Investments.  That was more than the combined profits of Goldman Sachs
Group Inc., JPMorgan Chase & Co., Citigroup Inc., Morgan
Stanley, Barclays Plc and HSBC Holdings Plc, the newspaper said.  Paulson & Co., run by  John Paulson , made $5.8 billion for
its investors after fees in the six months, ahead of George Soros’s Quantum Fund, which made $3 billion, the FT said.  The other eight funds are Bridgewater Pure Alpha, run by
Ray Dalio; Seth Klarman’s Baupost;  David Tepper ’s Appaloosa;
Bruce Kovner’s Caxton Global; Louis Bacon’s Moore Capital
Management; Alan Howard’s Brevan Howard Fund; Tom Steyer’s
Farallon; and Eddie Lampert’s ESL, the newspaper said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in London on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 